      "title": "Substitute the Fahrenheit temperature",
      "content": "The formula is $h=\\frac{9(v-273.15)}{5}+32$. Since $h=467.33$, write:<br/>$$467.33=\\frac{9(v-273.15)}{5}+32$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Undo the +32",
      "content": "Subtract $32$ from both sides:<br/>$$435.33=\\frac{9(v-273.15)}{5}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Undo the fraction",
      "content": "Multiply by $5$, then divide by $9$:<br/>$$2176.65=9(v-273.15)$$<br/>$$241.85=v-273.15$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for v",
      "content": "Add $273.15$:<br/>$$v=241.85+273.15=515$$"
    },
